        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Upma</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup semolina (sooji/rava)</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons oil or ghee</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon mustard seeds</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon urad dal</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon chana dal</li>
            <li>1/4 cup finely chopped onions</li>
            <li>1/4 cup finely chopped carrots</li>
            <li>1/4 cup green peas</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chopped bell peppers (optional)</li>
            <li>1/2 inch ginger, grated</li>
            <li>2 green chilies, chopped</li>
            <li>Curry leaves</li>
            <li>2.5 cups water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
            <li>Lemon wedges (optional, for serving)</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2> Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>breakfast</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Dry roast semolina in a pan over medium heat until it becomes aromatic and changes color slightly. Set aside.</li>
            <li>In the same pan, heat oil or ghee. Add mustard seeds, urad dal, and chana dal. Let them splutter.</li>
            <li>Add finely chopped onions, ginger, green chilies, and curry leaves. Saute until the onions turn translucent.</li>
            <li>Add chopped carrots, green peas, and bell peppers. Cook for a few minutes until the vegetables are slightly tender.</li>
            <li>Pour 2.5 cups of water into the pan. Bring it to a boil.</li>
            <li>Gradually add the roasted semolina, stirring continuously to avoid lumps.</li>
            <li>Reduce the heat to low, cover the pan, and let it simmer until the upma is cooked and has a thick consistency.</li>
            <li>Season with salt and garnish with fresh coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Serve hot upma with lemon wedges on the side (optional).</li>
            <li>Enjoy your flavorful Upma!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

